race.comment: ARTISTIC ENDEAVOUR (1) raced on the speed beaten 0.6 lengths over 1630m at Doomben as an equal favourite. This doesn't look as hard, and Rodd replaces the 3kg apprentice. Well placed to go one better. ISLA DELILAH (5)  improved last start when finding a couple better over 1350m at Ipswich beaten just 1.5 lengths. The step up in trip will suit and she has plenty of scope to improve. The Munce yard is going well. KOOLATAH QUEEN (6) wasn't beaten far in Listed grade before the spell but she's been plain her three runs back. Has been getting too far back and Moor will be looking to settle closer today. A chance if she does, LITTLE MISS CLASSY (7)  finished 3 lengths from the winner over 1630m at Doomben. Peaks and draws low. Appeals as a top-four contender. CARAMELFUDGESUNDAE (4) has been around the mark and the blinkers are on first time. Needs to find more to be winning.
